main event: A satellite (ECHO II) was observed over Kettering and Dayton, Ohio on September 17, 1965.
interesting points: The object was a white satellite that circled at 230 and 240 degrees, moving slowly with no sound.
The object moved to 190 degrees and then disappeared.
The witness described the object as being the size of a cart, approximately 25% the size of a cart.
The witness observed the object for about 30 minutes.
The witness was outdoors in a rural area when they observed the object.
